1. Program to check if a number is even or odd

   num=int(input("Enter the number to check even/odd: "))
   if (num%2==0):
      print("Number is even")
   else:
      print("Number is odd")


2. Program to accept name and salary. Check if their salary is >3L and display if they have to pay tax

   name=input("Enter the name of the employee: ")
   salary=int(input("Enter the salary of the employee: "))
   if (salary>300000):
      print("Pay the tax")
   else:
      print("No payment of tax required")


3. To find the largest of 3 numbers

   num1=int(input("Enter the first number: "))
   num2=int(input("Enter the second number: "))
   num3=int(input("Enter the third number: "))
   if (num1>num2 and num1>num3):
       print(f"{num1} is the greatest")
   elif (num2>num1 and num2>num3):
       print(f"{num2} is the greatest")
   else:
       print(f"{num3} is the greatest")


4. Program to check if a year given is a leap year or not

   year=int(input("Enter the year: "))
   if((year%400)==0):
       print(f"{year} is a leap year")
   else:
       print(f"{year} is not a leap year")


5. Write a program to accept a student’s name and scores in three subjects. Display the total, average,
   and class secured based on the following criteria:
   • 1st Class: Average score of 60 and above.
   • 2nd Class: Average score of 50 and above.
   • Pass Class: Average score of 35 and above.
   • Fail: Average score less than 35.

  
  name=input("Enter the name of the student: ")
english=int(input("Enter the marks in ENGLISH: "))
math=int(input("Enter the marks in MATH: "))
science=int(input("Enter the marks in SCIENCE: "))
sum=english+math+science
print(f"Total marks is {sum}")
average=sum/3
print(f"Average marks is {average}")
if((year%400)==0):
    print(f"{year} is a leap year")
else:
    print(f"{year} is not a leap year")
